720187f-c.title: Manhattan: Greenwich Street - Albany Street
720187f-c.text:
Greenwich Street, west side, north from Albany Street, showing at the
N.W. corner a 37 -story building formerly known as the Planters Hotel.
This building No. 122 Greenwich Street, was for a time a dry,goods
store; patronised by Henry Clay and other celebrites. Overhead, on
Greenwich Street, is the Ninth Ave. Elevated Line.
May 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same.
May 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(3)
A view eastward on Albany Street, and showing the side of the former
Planters Hotel. From that point, to the immediate foreground appear;
No. 3 (2-story structure); Nos. 5 and 7; all on Albany Street. Across
Greenwich Street, appears the Hamilton Building, No. 125-131 Greenwich
Street, at the S.E. corner of Thames Street.
May 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
